# Copy this file to .env.local (for local dev) and/or add these as
# Environment Variables in your Vercel project settings (for production).
# Vite only exposes variables prefixed with VITE_ to the browser.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Newsletter signup (src/components/Newsletter.jsx)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# QR Forge has no backend, so this is wired to Web3Forms (web3forms.com) —
# free, and it emails submissions straight to your inbox with no backend
# code needed. Until this is set, the newsletter form stays visible but
# tells users signups aren't connected yet — it never fakes a success
# message for an email that went nowhere.
#
# 1. Sign up free at https://web3forms.com and create a form.
# 2. Copy that form's "Access Key" (shown in your dashboard) — it looks
#    like b2177470-8fe7-4d8d-9887-87ebce25ebff.
# 3. Paste it below (locally) or as a Vercel Environment Variable
#    (production) — either way, name it exactly VITE_NEWSLETTER_ACCESS_KEY.
VITE_NEWSLETTER_ACCESS_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Contact form (src/pages/Contact.jsx)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Same idea as the newsletter above — also wired to Web3Forms. Create a
# SECOND, separate form on Web3Forms (so contact messages don't mix with
# newsletter signups), copy its Access Key, and set it here. Until it's
# set, the contact form tells the user honestly that it isn't connected
# yet, rather than pretending to send.
VITE_CONTACT_ACCESS_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Google AdSense (src/components/AdSlot.jsx, AdSenseLoader.jsx)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Leave both blank until your AdSense application is approved — every
# AdSlot on the site renders a harmless placeholder box until then, so
# there's nothing to "turn off" before applying.
#
# Once approved:
#   1. VITE_ADSENSE_CLIENT — your publisher ID, shown in AdSense under
#      Account > Account information (format: ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX).
#      Setting this alone loads the AdSense script site-wide.
#   2. Create an ad unit per placement in AdSense under Ads > By ad unit,
#      then pass its numeric slot id as the `slot` prop on that <AdSlot />
#      in code (e.g. <AdSlot slot="1234567890" />). A slot only goes live
#      once both the client ID and that unit's slot id are present.
#   3. Also replace the placeholder line in public/ads.txt with the exact
#      snippet AdSense shows you under Sites > [your site] > "ads.txt".
VITE_ADSENSE_CLIENT=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Analytics — Google Analytics 4 (src/components/AnalyticsLoader.jsx)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Off until set. Also respects the cookie consent banner — GA4 only loads
# after a visitor clicks "Accept", never before, and never at all without
# this variable set.
#
# Get your Measurement ID from GA4 under Admin > Data Streams > [your stream]
# (format: G-XXXXXXXXXX).
VITE_GA_MEASUREMENT_ID=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Error monitoring — Sentry (src/main.jsx)
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Off until set. Get a DSN by creating a free project at https://sentry.io
# (React platform). Without this, errors are only visible in each visitor's
# own browser console — you'd have no way to know something broke in
# production unless a user reports it.
VITE_SENTRY_DSN=
